\details{
Provides methods for querying KuCoin Futures public market data, including
contract details, tickers, orderbooks, trade history, klines, mark prices,
and funding rates. Inherits from \link{KucoinBase}.
\subsection{Purpose and Scope}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Contract Specifications}: Retrieve details for individual or all active futures contracts.
\item \strong{Real-Time Pricing}: Access tickers, orderbooks, and recent trade history.
\item \strong{Historical Data}: Fetch kline/candlestick data with automatic multi-page segmentation.
\item \strong{Funding Rates}: Query current and historical funding rates for perpetual contracts.
\item \strong{System Info}: Check server time and service status.
}
}

\subsection{Usage}{

Most endpoints are public and do not require authentication. The full
orderbook (\code{get_full_orderbook()}) is the only method that requires a
valid API key, secret, and passphrase. All other methods can be called
without credentials.
}

